.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-chat - Chat with a model hosted locally on this node


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel chat [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Chat with an AI model served locally on THIS node.

.PP
Discovers the inference engine(s) running on this machine (vLLM, Ollama,
llama.cpp, or Bonsai), lets you pick a model if more than one is available,
and opens an interactive streaming chat against its local API.

.PP
Thinking models (e.g. Bonsai) stream their reasoning separately from the
answer; the reasoning is shown dimmed and the answer in normal text.

.PP
Type your message and press Enter. Ctrl-C interrupts a streaming reply;
type /exit (or Ctrl-D) to quit.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--engine\fP=""
	Pre-select an engine by name (vllm, ollama, llamacpp, bonsai)

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for chat

.PP
\fB--max-tokens\fP=1024
	Max tokens to generate per reply

.PP
\fB--model\fP=""
	Pre-select a model by id

.PP
\fB--no-reasoning\fP[=false]
	Hide the model's chain-of-thought (thinking models only)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-auto-update\fP[=false]
	Disable automatic update checks and installs for this run (or set CITADEL_NO_AUTO_UPDATE=1)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel(1)\fP
